726919f-b.title: Queens: Hoyt Avenue - 27th Street
726919f-b.text:
Hoyt Avenue, north side, west from 27th Street. The
Grand Central Parkway approach to the Triborough Bridge was
later constructed here and numerous buildings demolished.
View 2 is west from Crescent Street and view 3 shows
some of the homes seen in view 1 being prepared for raning.
P. L. Sperr  Views 1,2: March, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 2: May 27, 1934

726918f-a.title: Queens: Hoyt Avenue - 27th Street
726918f-a.text:
Hoyt Avenue, north side, between 24th and Crescent Streets,
ohowint the back yards of homes fronting on 24th (left) and
Crescent Streets. Some of these will be torn down to make way
for the construction of the Triborough Bridge.
P. L. Sperr  May 27, 1934
NO REPRODUCTIONS

726920f-b.title: Queens: Hoyt Avenue - 27th Street
726920f-b.text:
Hoyt Avenue, north side, at 27th and 28th Streets,
showing the demolition of buildings for the construction
of the Queens approach of the Triborough Bridge. In the
background is the Hellgate Bridge. View 3 shows the Crys-
tal Gardens Apartments.
P. L. Sperr  Views 1,2: August 3, 1934
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 3: September 20, 1934
